This paper discusses compiler mappings for C and C++ atomics, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the current state of compilers and architectures in relation to the bug, which could fall under operating systems (cs.OS), cryptography and security (cs.CR), or software engineering (cs.SE).
